               <p>1674. <persName id="def1-1674-18430508" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1674-18430508" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1674-18430508" type="age" value="52"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1674-18430508" type="surname" value="MASON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1674-18430508" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN MASON</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18430508-1674-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18430508-1674-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="breakingPeace"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18430508-1674-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="wounding"></interp> for feloniously assaulting <persName id="t18430508-name-1424" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1424" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1424" type="surname" value="MASON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1424" type="given" value="ELLEN"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430508-1674-offence-1 t18430508-name-1424"></join>Ellen Mason</persName>, on the <rs id="t18430508-cd-254" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430508-1674-offence-1 t18430508-cd-254"></join>6th of May</rs>, and cutting and wounding her in and upon the left side of the head, with intent to do her some grievous bodily harm.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430508-name-1425" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1425" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1425" type="surname" value="MASON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1425" type="given" value="ELLEN"></interp>ELLEN MASON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the prisoner's wife, and live in Prince's-fields, Deptford. On Saturday night, the 6th of May, my husband came home, be<lb></lb>tween ten and eleven o'clock, drunk—we had a few words respecting his rela<lb></lb>tions—I rather provoked him, and was quite as much in fault as he was—I went towards the door—he followed me into the yard, and hit me in the face with his hand or fist, I am not sure which—I believe I took a piece of wood off the paling, and attempted to throw it at him, and he struck me twice with it on the side of my head—it did not knock me down—I was down at the time—I was not knocked down, I fell—I think I must have kicked my foot against a stone—my head felt very painful, and bled a great deal—I thought</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184305080185"></xptr>
               <p>something stuck in my head at the time—it was a bit of a nail—this is the stick—I have not been ill at all, or confined.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> I suppose all the injury done was from this nail? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—this is the piece of wood which I myself tore off, as my boy informed me—I was going to throw it at him when he took it from me—he had not got it in his hand when he came in—after he hit me in the face I struck him on the top of his hat—that was before he struck me with this.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430508-name-1426" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1426" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1426" type="surname" value="ANDREWS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1426" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY ANDREWS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of William Andrews, a pensioner at Deptford—I heard them quarrelling on this evening—I saw the prisoner striking his wife twice with this stick—he was going to strike a third blow, which I prevented—I was there at the beginning—he got the stick off my gate, and struck her on the head.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430508-name-1427" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1427" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1427" type="surname" value="DOWLING"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-1427" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD DOWLING</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a surgeon, and live at Deptford—I examined the prosecutrix, and found a slight wound on her head, as if made by a nail.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18430508-1674-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18430508-1674-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18430508-1674-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="lesserOffence"></interp>
                     <hi rend="smallCaps">GUILTY</hi> of an Assault.</rs> Aged 52.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18430508-1674-punishment-244" type="punishmentDescription">
